{"word":"συνηρεφής","slug":"συνηρεφής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνηρεφής</b></el> <el>(συν-ηρεφής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐρέφω'><el>ἐρέφω</el></a>\n<p/><i>thickly covered</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>:— <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ξυνηρεφὲς πρόσωπον</el> her <i>clouded</i> face, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}